      "id": "spine_biology_l4_clonal_selection_principle",
      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_adaptive_immunity_overview",
      "content": {
        "title": "Clonal Selection and Affinity Maturation",
        "definition": "Antigen-driven proliferation and differentiation of lymphocytes bearing antigen-specific receptors, with somatic hypermutation refining antibody affinity in germinal centers.",
        "summary": "Clonal selection explains how a vast receptor repertoire yields a focused response. Affinity maturation improves antibody quality during secondary responses."
      },
