      "resolution_level": 5,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_adaptive_immunity_overview",
      "content": {
        "title": "Central vs Effector Memory T Cells",
        "definition": "Memory T-cell subsets distinguished by lymphoid homing versus peripheral tissue surveillance, with different recall kinetics and effector potential.",
        "summary": "Central memory T cells (CCR7+) circulate through lymph nodes for rapid reactivation. Effector memory T cells (CCR7−) provide immediate tissue surveillance."
